		<title>13Road Safety in Congleton</title>
		<content>  'Chronicle' news 14/6/85 (cont)      
{                                      
{Safer way for cyclists to turn right  
                                       
                                       
   Over one third of road accidents    
 involving child cyclists are          
 associated with right turns.          
                                       
   Instead of the present manouvre     
 which involves  crossing the paths of 
 other vehicles and at times waiting in
 the centre of the road, cyclists will 
 be trained to  pull into the side of  
 the road on the approach to the       
 junction and then to cross the road as
 a pedestrian.                         
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
